A

tan(alpha) = BC / AB

|-------+------------|
| alpha | tan(alpha) |
|-------+------------|
|     0 |          0 |
|     1 |       0.02 |
|     5 |       0.09 |
|    10 |       0.18 |
|    15 |       0.27 |
|  22.5 |       0.41 |
|    30 |       0.58 |
|  37.5 |       0.77 |
|    45 |          1 |
|-------+------------|
AB = 1 => BC = 1 * tan(alpha)
BC = 1 => AB = 1 / tan(alpha)
